                  <summary><p>Poems by <persName xml:lang="ta" role="author">Tāyumāṉavar</persName>. Entitled <title xml:lang="ta">Tiruppāṭaṟṟiraṭṭu</title> (U3, <locus facs="7">f[1]r, c1, line 1</locus>) and <title xml:lang="ta">Tāyumāṉavacuvāmikaḷ Pāṭal</title> (U4, <locus facs="9">f[1]r, lm2, lines 4-6)</locus>; U5, <locus facs="321">f155r, c2, line 1)</locus>).</p>
<p>Appears to be a palm-leaf copy of a book printed in 1836. See <locus facs="7">U3</locus>.</p>

<p>Description based on the examination of the original manuscript (February 2023).</p>
<p>Dimensions assessed at the time of examination.</p>   </summary>
                  
